=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_MoogLadder_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 60 Hz, featuring moderate attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, and filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: moderate
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: moderate
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 60.1513
  harmonic_decay_rate: -1.3441
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0150
  pitch_clarity: 39.7202
  inharmonicity: 0.0026
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -26.6876
  resonance_freq: 150.7324

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: MoogLadder Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/MoogLadder.html
// Tags: MoogLadder, Classes, filter
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
{ MoogLadder.ar(Mix(LFSaw.ar([120, 180], 0, 0.33)), LinExp.kr(LFCub.kr(0.1, 0.5*pi), -1, 1, 180, 8500), 0.75).dup }.play
